title: Travel_Management_altA
name: Travel_Management_altA
description:
Draft Resource Management Plan and Environmental Impact Statement, published December 2012
This data set consists of digital spatial data describing
Off Highway Vehicle Designations within the Grand Junction
Field Office area. Source: Alternative A data derived from: T:\CO\GIS\gisdata\field_offices\gjfo\recreation\OHV.gdb\OHV. Data used to describe GJFO RMP travel mananagement alternative A. Boundaries slightly adjusted by EMPSi Marcia Rickey in order to make data topology match GJFO RMP land status.

CLOSED = Closed to Motorized Vehicles
Limited to designated for mechan* = Limited to Designated Routes for Foot, Horse & Mechanized (Closed to Motorized Use)
EXISTING ROADS = Limited to Existing Routes for Motorized Vehicles
DESIGNATED SEASONAL =Seasonal Closure for Motorized Vehicles
EXISTING SEASONAL =  Seasonal Closure for Motorized Vehicles
OPEN = Open to All Modes of Travel
HIGH_USE = Open (Intensive) to All Modes of Travel
DESIGNATED ROADS = Limited to Designated Routes for Motorized Vehicles

author.source: Grand Junction Field Office, Bureau of Land Management
